    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 4-5 min, break the <strong>basa</strong> into chunks in the pan with a wooden spoon and stir it through the rice</p><p>Cook, covered, for 1-2 min further or until the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once cooked, add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and stir it all together until fully combined – this is your <strong>smoked basa & spinach pilau rice</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
